<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-077-385 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 173 377</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  August 26 1991 v13 n34 p50(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Lotus 1-2-3 Release 2.3. (Software Review) (one of two evaluationsm of spreadsheets running on 80286-based hardware in 'Spreadsheetson 286s') (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Walkenbach, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Lotus Development Corp's 1-2-3 2.3 spreadsheet offers mousesupport, bundled add-ins and an optional graphical user interface.andO;Formula/analysis performance is satisfactory; the program has manybuilt-in functions but does not support user-defined functions.andO;Compatibility is good, and recalculation speed is very good.andP;  Theprogram does not use overlays and accesses the disk only to saveor retrieve files.andP;  Database and graphics performance earnsatisfactory scores.andP;  Output is excellent but requires the WYSIWYGadd-in.andP;  Macros are satisfactory, as is consolidation and linkingperformance.andP;  Capacity is poor; some key features, such as Undo,do not work on a 640Kbyte system.andP;  Network performance issatisfactory.andP;  Documentation is very good; the package hasquick-start, quick-reference and users' guides, an upgrader'smanual and function and macro references.andP;  The help window is nowcontext-sensitive.andP;  Ease of learning and ease of use aresatisfactory.andP;  Support policies are very good; Lotus provides 90days of unlimited toll-free support as well as fax and BBSsupport.andP;  Technical support is poor; technicians are competent butdifficult to reach.andP;  Lotus 1-2-3 2.3 is a good value at $495.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Lotus Development Corp. (Products).andO;Ticker:    LOTS.andO;Product:   Intel 80286 (Microprocessor) (evaluation)Lotus 1-2-3 2.3 (Spreadsheet software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     SpreadsheetsEvaluationSoftware packagesLow Performance Equipment.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>